 M http://src.chromium.org/viewvc/chrome/trunk/src/native_client/SConstruct?r1=5626&amp;r2=5625&amp;pathrev=5626

Scons: Disable the Windows crash dialog box by default

This means that crashes in tests -- or in Scons' Python process itself
-- won't hang on Buildbot.  This is needed so that we can run the
tests with signal handling (the '-S' option) disabled by default, so
that we can test what we ship.

We make this optional in case the crash dialog is useful for
debugging.

BUG=http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1914
TEST=run_execute_data_test (with '-S' removed in SConstruct)

